verbose_text: The EEW value of DGE in the solution was determined using equation (1), 63 (1) EEW = M/f (B-S) where M is the mass (g) of DGE, f is the NaOH concentration (M), B is the amount of NaOH solution (mL) in the blank sample, and S is the amount of NaOH solution (mL) used for the dodecyl glycidyl ether sample.
